_From [moritzp...@gmail.com](https://code.google.com/u/110380137820502036004/) on February 05, 2011 18:14:38_

When requesting an action it is expected to get a vanilla action without anything set but the params the user provided when getting it.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Obtain any kind of Action and set a OnActionCompleted listener
2. Let the action executed so that it is finished (back in the pool)
3. Get a new action of the same type. It has the previously set listener

The following snippet shows the problem. The sysout should print null all the time.

=== Snippet ===

public class Test implements ApplicationListener {

```
private Stage stage;

private Image image;

class Listener implements OnActionCompleted {

    public void completed(final Action action) {
        // do stuff
    }

}

public void create() {
    stage = new Stage(400, 400, false);

    image = new Image("img", new Texture(Gdx.files.internal("textures/black.png")));
    stage.addActor(image);
}

public void resume() {
}

public void render() {

    ScaleTo scale = ScaleTo.$(1.0f, 1.0f, 0.1f);
    System.out.println(scale.getCompletionListener());

    scale.setCompletionListener(new Listener());

    image.action(scale);

    stage.act(Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime());
}

public void resize(final int width, final int height) {
}

public void pause() {
}

public void dispose() {
}
```

}

_Original issue: http://code.google.com/p/libgdx/issues/detail?id=117_

